How to install and run Pollo
============================

Make sure you have the most recent Java JDK from the 1.3 series,
especially if you're running Linux (IBM reguraly updates its
JDK).

For Windows platforms
=====================
- put the directory containing java.exe in the path, or
  adjust the file run.bat
- start the file run.bat

For Linux/Unix platforms
========================
- unzip the distribution zip file with jar: jar xvf pollo.zip
- make sure the $JAVA_HOME/bin directory is in the PATH.
- make run.sh executable: chmod u+x run.sh
- ./run.sh
